It provides them with opportunities to gain practical experience in running and managing a retail shop. Merchandise on sale include clothes, fashion accessories, electronics, snacks and other interesting items, all of which are sourced by the students

properties.NAME: Career Services Centre
properties.DESCRIPTION: At Career Services, our focus is to help our students develop their self-concept and deepen their understanding and commitment towards the sectors that they are likely to enter after they graduate, to successfully transit to work.

properties.NAME: School of Business (BUS)
properties.DESCRIPTION: Your time in our School of Business (BUS) will transform you into a resourceful, innovative and enterprising professional – one who is always ready to take on dynamic challenges and achieve success in today’s fast-paced and globalised business environment.

properties.NAME: School of Design (DES)
properties.DESCRIPTION: Our School of Design (DES) has built a strong reputation as an award-winning school. Here, you will get exposed to the rapid changes in trends, thinking, and concepts of the design world, which will prepare you to join the ranks of design practitioners in Singapore and abroad!

properties.NAME: School of Informatics & IT (IIT)
properties.DESCRIPTION: From cybersecurity and financial technologies to big data and games design, and more, our School of Informatics & IT (IIT) will show you how you can leverage on the myriad of IT uses to help improve business processes, ensure efficiency and enrich lives.

properties.NAME: School of Engineering (ENG)
properties.DESCRIPTION: Our School of Engineering (ENG) is always at the forefront of technology. With state of the art facilities and industry-relevant curricula, the knowledge and training you will receive here is the edge you need to realise your engineering ambitions.

properties.NAME: School of Humanities & Social Sciences (HSS)
properties.DESCRIPTION: Our School of Humanities & Social Sciences (HSS), in its offer of people-oriented specialisations, firmly believes in fostering a caring culture with a community spirit in an academic environment. Get ready to explore meaningful career opportunities and make a difference to society, here!

properties.NAME: Temasek Convention Centre (TCC) and Foyer
properties.DESCRIPTION: 1240-seat Temasek Convention Centre

properties.NAME: Temasek Tourism Academy (TTA)
properties.DESCRIPTION: Hospitality & Tourism Management (HTM) and Leisure & Events Management (LEM) students will enjoy and experience hands-on training at the seven-storey Temasek Tourism Academy (TTA). Fronting the scenic Bedok Reservoir, the TTA comprises a lobby and its observation room, learning suite, tourism technology rooms, layout room, event hall, and event management ideation rooms among others. The TTA collaborates with key industry partners such as lodging operation @ Four Seasons Training Suite and Amadeus GDS Training @ lab to ensure that learning is at the forefront for tourism and leisure education.

properties.NAME: Centre for Aquaculture & Veterinary Science (CAVS) TP Animal Clinic & Wellness
properties.DESCRIPTION: TP Animal Clinic & Wellness with its spacious design features 2 consultation rooms, a surgical operating suite, in-house laboratory capabilities, digital radiography services, isolation wards, a physiotherapy room with extensive exercise equipment, animal holding areas, a land treadmill and a hydro-treadmill.

properties.NAME: CIA Top Table
properties.HOURS: Lunch only on Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Thursdays. (11:30am to 1:30pm)   Dinner only on Fridays and Saturdays. (6:00pm to 9:30pm)   *Closed on Sundays, Mondays and Public Holidays.    Operating Period: Late-August to Early-November every year.
properties.DESCRIPTION: The CIA Top Table Restaurant is operated by students of the Culinary Institute of America taking their Bachelor of Business Administration in Food Business Management where they acquire hands-on experience working in the front and back of the house from August to early-November. A Contemporary Italian Menu is typically served from August till the end of September, and from October to early-November, a Formal French Dining experience is offered. Reservations for CIA Top Table Restaurant are available through Chope under "CIA SG Dining". For further enquiries contact: ciasg.dining@culinary.edu

properties.NAME: Triangular Gardens
properties.DESCRIPTION: At the Garden Fiesta, you can find food outlets such as Triplets, McDonalds and Subway.

properties.NAME: Library
properties.DESCRIPTION: Standing at ten storeys tall, the TP library is open to current TP students, staff & members. The library provides a wide range of information resources, services & facilities under one roof to support teaching and learning. Our friendly staff can assist with on-the-spot research queries and advice on using relevant and credible resources. Individuals interested in using the library’s facilities and materials may apply for external membership.

properties.NAME: Glocal Connect Village (GCV)
properties.DESCRIPTION: Glocal Connect Village (GCV) at Temasek Polytechnic (TP) is a one-of-a-kind, iconic representation of the poly's internationalisation strategy. Apart from being a vibrant learning space for local and international staff and students, GCV will also be a platform for these groups, local budding artists and the community to immerse in and showcase cultural diversity through artistic talent

properties.NAME: Temasek Culinary Academy / The Culinary Institute of America
properties.HOURS: Mondays to Fridays: 8:30am – 5pm  Closed on Saturdays, Sundays and Public Holidays  *Closed during the month of December
properties.DESCRIPTION: The Culinary Institute of America, the world’s premier culinary college located on the campus of Temasek Polytechnic, offers its renowned Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA) in Food Business Management for polytechnic diploma holders. The objectives for the bachelor’s degree program at CIA Singapore are ambitious—to build essential knowledge and skills, foster the ability to solve problems and think creatively, and prepare our students for future leadership in the foodservice and hospitality industry. If you are currently enrolled in or graduated from one of the five polytechnics, you can apply online at the Singapore Institute of Technology website. Admission Enquiries: adm@singaporetech.edu.sg

properties.DESCRIPTION: The Top Table is a full-service restaurant operated by Business Diploma students, located on Level 3 of the Temasek Culinary Academy. This contemporary restaurant offers set menus designed to train students in the finer aspects of restaurant service and cuisine.
